-- Leicester Tigers, Harlequins Advance to Premiership Rugby Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-12T18:57:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-12/leicester-tigers-harlequins-advance-to-premiership-rugby-final.html
Leicester Tigers  secured their eighth
consecutive appearance in the English Premiership rugby final,
where they will meet Harlequins.  Alesana Tuilagi and Steve Mafi scored one try each and
George Ford kicked 14 points in Leicester’s 24-15 semifinal win
over defending champion Saracens.  Joe Marler’s 77th-minute try, converted by Nick Evans,
completed a 10-point rally in the final eight minutes that gave
Harlequins a 25-23 win over the  Northampton Saints .  Leicester and Harlequins will meet May 26 at Twickenham
Stadium in London. It will be the ninth final appearance for the
Tigers, while Harlequins will be playing in the title match for
the first time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  